<TITLE> Car bomb in Iraq's Hilla kills 22 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BAGHDAD, July 24 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide car bomb killed 22 people and wounded 66 in a crowded market in the Iraqi town of Hilla on Tuesday, police said. Police said the market was also close to a maternity hospital in the Shia town, 100 km (60 miles) south of Baghdad. The explosion set at least 10 cars ablaze, police said. Tens of thousands of US and Iraqi soldiers have been engaged in a series of offensives in and around Baghdad to try to stem car bomb attacks, which are mainly blamed on the Sunni Islamist organisation al Qaeda in Iraq. bdn
